                        <interp inst="t18560707-name-165" type="given" value="ALFRED"></interp>ALFRED GREEN</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">policeman</hi>). I produce a certificate of the prisoner's former conviction from Mr. Clark's office—(<hi rend="italic">Bead: "Central Criminal Court, Jan.</hi> 7, 1852; <hi rend="italic">James Jerrard, Convicted of receiving brass, having been before convicted; Transported for seven years</hi>)"—the prisoner is the person—I had him in custody.</p>
